24 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 2024 Supp. 32-1420 is hereby amended to read as
25 follows: 32-1420. (a) There is hereby established a state matching grant
26 program to provide assistance in the promotion of tourism and
27 development of quality tourist attractions within the state of Kansas.
28 Grants awarded under this program shall be limited to not more than 40%
29 of the cost of any proposed project. Applicants shall not utilize any state
30 moneys to meet the matching requirements under the provisions of this
31 program. Both public and private entities shall be eligible to apply for a
32 grant under the provisions of this act. Not less than 75% 50% of all
33 moneys granted under this program shall be allocated to public entities or
34 entities exempt from taxation under the provisions of 501(c)(3) of the
35 federal internal revenue code of 1986, and amendments thereto. No more
36 than 20% of moneys granted to public or nonprofit entities shall be granted
37 to any single such entity. Furthermore, no more than 20% of moneys
38 granted to private entities shall be granted to any single such entity. The
39 secretary of commerce shall administer the provisions of this act and the
40 secretary may adopt rules and regulations establishing criteria for
41 qualification for a matching grant and such other matters deemed
42 necessary by the secretary for the administration of this act.
43 (b) For the purpose of K.S.A. 32-1420 through 32-1422, and

